Package environment.law

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Law
    An interface for laws, being objects used by the reactor to validate certain influences.
    PerceptionLaw
    An interface for perceptionLaws, being objects used by PerceptionReactor to alter perception by Agents.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LawPassPacket
    A law controlling the passing of packets.
    LawPickCrumb
    A law controlling the picking up of crumbs.
    LawPickPacket
    A law controlling the picking up of Packets.
    LawPutFlag
    A law controlling the putting down of Flags.
    LawPutPacket
    A law controlling the putting down of packets.
    LawPutPheromone
    A law controlling the putting down of Pheromones.
    LawStep
    A law controlling the movement of agents.
    PercLawSeeNothing
    A PerceptionLaw that doesn't allow an agent to perceive 'any' specific information.
    PercLawWallObstacle
    A PerceptionLaw for not allowing agents to perceive Items that are situated behind a Wall Item from their point of view.
